  "text": "## gRPC Error Status Propagation Across Go Services\n\n### kubernetes/kubernetes\n\n**Error Creation Pattern:**\nKubernetes creates gRPC status errors using `google.golang.org/grpc/status.Error()` and `status.Errorf()` with specific error codes:\n- `codes.ResourceExhausted` for rate limiting (pkg/kubelet/apis/grpc/ratelimit.go)\n- `codes.NotFound` for missing resources (test/e2e/storage/drivers/csi-test/mock/service/*.go)\n- `codes.InvalidArgument` for validation failures (staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/server.go)\n- `codes.Unimplemented` for unsupported operations (test/images/agnhost/grpc-health-checking/grpc-health-checking.go)\n\n**Error Translation to HTTP:**\nTwo main mechanisms translate gRPC errors to HTTP responses:\n\n1. **CRI Streaming Layer** (staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/errors.go):\n   - `WriteError()` function converts gRPC status codes to HTTP status codes\n   - Maps: `codes.NotFound` → `http.StatusNotFound`, `codes.ResourceExhausted` → `http.StatusTooManyRequests`\n   - Default: `http.StatusInternalServerError` for unknown codes\n   - Handles special cases like `Retry-After` header for rate limiting\n\n2. **gRPC-Gateway** (vendor/github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2/runtime/errors.go):\n   - `HTTPStatusFromCode()` provides comprehensive mapping of all gRPC codes to HTTP status codes\n   - Implements the Google RPC code mapping standard\n   - Used in gateway handler (vendor/github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2/runtime/handler.go)\n\n**Error Handling Pattern:**\nKubernetes also extracts and checks status codes from errors using `status.FromError()` (staging/src/k8s.io/cri-api/pkg/errors/errors.go) with `IsNotFound()` helper function.\n\n### grafana/grafana\n\n**Error Creation Pattern:**\nGrafana creates gRPC status errors in authentication and authorization layers:\n- `codes.Unauthenticated` for missing/invalid tokens (pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/auth.go)\n- `codes.Unauthenticated` for invalid credentials (pkg/storage/unified/resource/grpc/authenticator.go, pkg/services/authz/zanzana/server/auth.go)\n- `codes.NotFound` for unsupported resources (pkg/services/authz/rbac/service.go)\n\nAll created using `status.Error()` and `status.Errorf()` with descriptive messages.\n\n**Error Translation to Backend Status:**\nGrafana converts gRPC status codes to internal backend status codes (pkg/tsdb/influxdb/fsql/fsql.go):\n- `codes.InvalidArgument` → `backend.StatusBadRequest`\n- `codes.PermissionDenied` → `backend.StatusForbidden`\n- `codes.NotFound` → `backend.StatusNotFound`\n- `codes.Unavailable` → `http.StatusServiceUnavailable`\n- `codes.Unauthenticated` → `backend.StatusUnauthorized`\n- Default: `backend.StatusInternal` for other codes\n\nThis is done by checking error status using `status.FromError()` and switching on code type.\n\n### etcd-io/etcd\n\n**Error Definition Pattern:**\netcd defines comprehensive pre-allocated gRPC status errors (api/v3rpc/rpctypes/error.go) with specific codes:\n- `codes.InvalidArgument` for parameter validation errors (ErrGRPCEmptyKey, ErrGRPCValueProvided)\n- `codes.FailedPrecondition` for state constraint violations (ErrGRPCLeaseExist, ErrGRPCMemberExist)\n- `codes.NotFound` for missing resources (ErrGRPCLeaseNotFound, ErrGRPCMemberNotFound)\n- `codes.OutOfRange` for boundary violations (ErrGRPCCompacted, ErrGRPCFutureRev)\n- `codes.ResourceExhausted` for quota limits (ErrGRPCNoSpace, ErrGRPCRequestTooManyRequests)\n- `codes.Unavailable` for temporary failures (ErrGRPCNoLeader, ErrGRPCTimeout)\n- `codes.DataLoss` for corruption (ErrGRPCCorrupt)\n- `codes.PermissionDenied` for authorization failures (ErrGRPCPermissionDenied)\n- `codes.Unauthenticated` for authentication failures (ErrGRPCInvalidAuthToken)\n- `codes.Canceled` for cancellation (ErrGRPCWatchCanceled, ErrGRPCCanceled)\n- `codes.DeadlineExceeded` for timeouts (ErrGRPCDeadlineExceeded)\n\n**Error Translation Pattern:**\netcd translates internal errors to gRPC errors using a mapping system (server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/util.go):\n- `togRPCError()` function converts internal domain errors to pre-defined gRPC status errors\n- Maintains mapping in `toGRPCErrorMap` from internal errors (membership, mvcc, auth, etc.) to gRPC errors\n- Falls back to `status.Error(codes.Unknown, ...)` for unmapped errors\n- Special handling for context errors (context.Canceled → codes.Canceled, context.DeadlineExceeded → codes.DeadlineExceeded)\n\n**Error Checking Pattern:**\netcd client and proxy layers check status codes using `status.FromError()` to determine retry behavior and error handling:\n- `client/v3/retry.go`: Checks if error is retryable based on code (e.g., unavailable, internal)\n- `client/v3/watch.go`: Checks for FailedPrecondition to handle cancellation\n- `client/v3/client.go`: Determines retry eligibility by checking code != Unavailable && code != Internal\n- `server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` and `lease.go`: Check for Canceled code to detect connection closure\n\n### Cross-Repository Patterns\n\n**Common Pattern:**\n1. **Error Creation**: All three repos use `google.golang.org/grpc/status.Error()` or `.Errorf()` with specific codes\n2. **Error Propagation**: Errors flow from business logic → gRPC handlers → transport layer\n3. **Status Extraction**: `status.FromError()` extracts status info for inspection\n4. **Code-Based Handling**: Switch statements on `status.Code()` determine behavior\n5. **Translation**: Each repo handles translation differently:\n   - Kubernetes: Uses both simple switch (CRI) and comprehensive mapping (gRPC-Gateway)\n   - Grafana: Maps to internal backend status codes\n   - etcd: Pre-allocates all errors with codes, maps internal errors → gRPC errors\n\n**Key Difference:**\netcd's approach of pre-defining all errors in a centralized registry (rpctypes/error.go) and maintaining explicit mappings differs from Kubernetes' and Grafana's inline error creation patterns. This makes etcd's error handling more consistent and easier to audit."
